            "id": "4492509",
            "title": "MediaAlpha buys back $32.9 mln in shares from Insignia Capital",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li><span class=\"location\">MediaAlpha (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MAX\" title=\"MediaAlpha, Inc.\">MAX</a></span>) said on Thursday that it has repurchased 3.23 million shares of its Class A common stock for approximately $32.9 million in a privately negotiated deal with entities affiliated with Insignia Capital Group.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"location\">The repurchase price of $10.17 per share reflects a 5.5% discount to MediaAlpha’s closing stock price on September 2, 2025.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"location\">The deal, approved by a special committee of independent directors, involved Insignia exchanging an equal number of Class B shares and Class B-1 units in company's QL Holdings, LLC subsidiary for the Class A shares. The repurchased shares will be canceled and retired.</span></li>\n<li>“Privately repurchasing these shares at a discount is immediately accretive,\" CFO Thompson, said in a statement.</li>\n<li>MAX <span style=\"color: green;\">+1.92%</span> after hours to $12.21.</li>\n<li>Source: <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20222254-mediaalpha-announces-32_9-million-private-stock-repurchase\">Press Release</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
