            "id": "4492512",
            "title": "Cipher Mining generates 13% more bitcoin in August vs. July",
            "description": "<html><body><p>Cipher Mining (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CIFR\" title=\"Cipher Mining Inc.\">CIFR</a></span>) <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20222236-cipher-mining-announces-august-2025-operational-update\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"produced\">produced</a> 241 bitcoin (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BTC-USD\" title=\"Bitcoin USD\">BTC-USD</a>) in August, surpassing the prior month's 214 mined in July, it said on Thursday.</p>\n<p>It sold 42 bitcoin (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BTC-USD\" title=\"Bitcoin USD\">BTC-USD</a>) during the month, holding a total of 1,414 tokens.</p>\n<p>Its operating hashrate advanced to 23.0 at the end of August exahashes per second (EH/s) from 20.4 at end-July.</p>\n<p>Black Pearl Phase I continued to scale production this month, accounting for about 39% of Cipher’s (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CIFR\" title=\"Cipher Mining Inc.\">CIFR</a></span>) total bitcoin mined last month, as new rigs continued to be delivered.</p>\n</body></html>",
