            "id": "4492516",
            "title": "Howard Hughes Holdings reports $1.2B of sales at Ward Village launch",
            "description": "<html><body><p>Howard Hughes Communities, the real estate platform of Howard Hughes Holdings (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/HHH\" title=\"Howard Hughes Holdings Inc.\">HHH</a></span>), <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20222328-howard-hughes-communities-reports-1_2-billion-in-sales-at-launch-of-newest-luxury-residential\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"reported $1.2B in sales at the launch\">reported $1.2B in sales at the launch</a> of two residential towers at Ward Village in Honolulu, according to a company statement on Thursday.</p>\n<p>The total included $280M in penthouse sales, with a single residence selling in excess of $40M. Robust sales at the ‘Ilima tower, being developed in partnership with Discovery Land Co., is 41% pres-sold and the Melia tower is 52% pre-sold as of Sept. 1, 2025, indicating continued demand for luxury condominiums, the company said.</p>\n<p>\"The record sales at ‘Ilima and Melia — both in volume and pricing — are the highest ever seen in Hawai‘i, solidifying Ward Village as the gold standard for luxury living on O‘ahu,\" said David R. O’Reilly, CEO of Howard Hughes (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/HHH\" title=\"Howard Hughes Holdings Inc.\">HHH</a></span>). </p>\n<p>Howard Hughes Holdings (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/HHH\" title=\"Howard Hughes Holdings Inc.\">HHH</a></span>) stock<span style=\"color: #008000;\"> rose 0.4% </span>in after-hours trading.</p>\n</body></html>",
